Package liquid.gui

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConsolePanel
    Class contains a text box area used to print textual information about the simulation.
    EnviroAddiParamPanel
    Class creates the additional parameters of the EnvironmentEditorPanel.
    EnviroFlowmetersAndBreakpointsPanel
    Class is a branch of the EnvironmentEditorPanel.
    EnvironmentEditorPanel
    Class stores the details of the EnvironmentEditorPanel section of the ParameterPanel class.
    EnviroObstaclesAndDrainsPanel
    Class is a branch of the EnvironmentEditorPanel.
    EnviroPanel
    Class is a branch of the EnvironmentEditorPanel.
    EnviroSourcesPanel
    Class is a branch of the EnvironmentEditorPanel.
    LiquidFrame
    Class creates the overall frame of the simulator.
    LiquidGUI
    LiquidGUI is the central class of the GUI, where all components of the GUI are initialized here and available for other components to access them when necessary.
    LiquidGuiVariables
    Class will store all of the parameters associated with the simulation.
    LiquidMenuBar
    Class creates the menu bar along the top of the simulator.
    ParameterPanel
    Sets up some of the parameters to be used during the simulation, all changeable by the user.
    SimulationPanel
    Class creates a panel to display the simulation itself.
    VariousMessages
    Class stores all of the JOptionPane messages for the other classes to use and display.
